The course deals with the concept and scope of labour law; conclusion and termination of the employment contract; the rights, duties and liability of the parties to the employment contract (incl. working and rest time, holidays, remuneration, etc.); as well as collective labour relations and the resolution of labour disputes.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide understanding about labour law regulation and practice in Estonia.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completing the course, a student: *knows the legal regulation of labour relations in Estonia and its connections with the EU labour law; *knows problems arising when implementing labour law acts and possibilities to solve them; *is able to resolve labour disputes.
